'''William Kropp''' (born March 12, 1990) is an American [[professional golfer]] who plays on [[PGA Tour Latinoamérica]].<ref name=ptla>{{cite web |url=http://www.pgatourla.com/golfers/301022/profile/?lg=en |title=William Kropp – Player Profile |publisher=[[PGA Tour Latinoamérica]] |access-date=April 25, 2014 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140405010813/http://www.pgatourla.com/golfers/301022/profile/?lg=en |archive-date=April 5, 2014}}</ref>

Kropp turned professional in 2013 after having captained the [[Oklahoma Sooners]] golf team during his senior year at the [[University of Oklahoma]]. Kropp's first professional win came at the 2013 OK Kids Korral Championship on the [[Adams Pro Tour]].<ref name=OKKids>{{cite web |url=http://agpts.bluegolf.com/bluegolf/agpt13/event/agpt1312/contest/1/leaderboard.htm |title=OK Kids Korral Championship – 2013 Leaderboard |publisher=BlueGolf |accessdate=April 25, 2014}}</ref>

The win and other performances in 2013 earned Kropp his membership on [[PGA Tour Latinoamérica]] for the 2014 season.<ref name=ptla /> Kropp was quickly able to capitalize achieving his first win on the tour at the [[Abierto OSDE del Centro]] in just his fifth start on the tour.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.pgatourla.com/event/m2014070/?lg=en#.U1rGHFw37eI |title=Oklahoma's William Kropp holds off Cabrera to win in Cordoba |publisher=[[PGA Tour]] |accessdate=April 25, 2014}}</ref> With this win, Kropp moved to number 617 and inside the top 1000 on the [[Official World Golf Ranking]] for the first time in his career.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.owgr.com/Ranking/PlayerProfile.aspx?playerId=18193 |title=Official World Golf Ranking – Player Profile |publisher=[[Official World Golf Ranking]] |accessdate=April 25, 2014}}</ref> He also finished third at the [[Stella Artois Open]] and fifth at the [[Dominican Republic Open]] and tenth at the [[Brazil Open (golf)|Brazil Open]], ending tenth in the Order of Merit.

